{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852297885,"sessionID":"ses_286f4e666ffednMOyI47LTqQHL","part":{"id":"prt_d790b967d001gWUdXpaTWZnxVK","messageID":"msg_d790b7707001wt2EZgD2R9a0Zc","sessionID":"ses_286f4e666ffednMOyI47LTqQHL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-42f9a55e664c42399f6e2de653af4e37","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/config.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/config.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: type Config struct {\n4: \tPort                  string\n5: \tEnableTLS             bool\n6: \tTLSCert               string\n7: \tTLSKey                string\n8: \tMaxConcurrentRequests int\n9: \tDebug                 bool\n10: }\n11: \n12: func DefaultConfig() *Config {\n13: \treturn &Config{\n14: \t\tPort:                  \":8080\",\n15: \t\tEnableTLS:             false,\n16: \t\tMaxConcurrentRequests: 1000,\n17: \t\tDebug:                 false,\n18: \t}\n19: }\n\n(End of file - total 19 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\ntype Config struct {\n\tPort                  string\n\tEnableTLS             bool\n\tTLSCert               string\n\tTLSKey                string\n\tMaxConcurrentRequests int\n\tDebug                 bool\n}\n\nfunc DefaultConfig() *Config {\n\treturn &Config{\n\t\tPort:                  \":8080\",\n\t\tEnableTLS:             false,\n\t\tMaxConcurrentRequests: 1000,\n\t\tDebug:                 false,\n\t}\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/config.go","time":{"start":1775852297868,"end":1775852297884}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852297888,"sessionID":"ses_286f4e666ffednMOyI47LTqQHL","part":{"id":"prt_d790b9ac4001EMnmuqRV8PDruD","messageID":"msg_d790b7707001wt2EZgD2R9a0Zc","sessionID":"ses_286f4e666ffednMOyI47LTqQHL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e82a3011de3d4185b9ae5ee803587555","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Server type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Server struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `config *Config` for server configuration\n26:   - `engine *gin.Engine` for Gin HTTP framework\n27:   - `httpServer *http.Server` for underlying HTTP server\n28:   - `sessionManager SessionManager` for session resolution\n29:   - `store Store` for session state persistence\n30:   - `jwtManager JWTManager` for JWT token generation\n31:   - `transport *http.Transport` for HTTP transport sharing\n32:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Config struct definition\n35: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n36: - **WHEN** reading the `Config` struct\n37: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n38:   - `Port int` for listening port (default 8080)\n39:   - `EnableTLS bool` for TLS enablement\n40:   - `TLSCert string` for TLS certificate file path\n41:   - `TLSKey string` for TLS private key file path\n42:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` for concurrency limit\n43:   - `Debug bool` for debug mode\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: NewServer constructor\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n47: - **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config *Config, sessionManager SessionManager, store Store, jwtManager JWTManager, logger Logger)`\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Server` with:\n49:   - `engine` initialized with `gin.New()`\n50:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` if `config.Debug == false`\n51:   - `gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)` if `config.Debug == true`\n52:   - `transport` initialized with shared HTTP transport\n53:   - `httpServer` initialized with h2c configuration\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: DefaultConfig\n56: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n57: - **WHEN** calling `DefaultConfig()`\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Config` with:\n59:   - `Port` = `8080`\n60:   - `EnableTLS` = `false`\n61:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests` = `1000`\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Requirement: Server lifecycle\n66: \n67: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods with graceful shutdown.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Start without TLS\n70: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == false`\n71: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n72: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServe()` SHALL be called\n73: - AND h2c server SHALL handle HTTP/2 without TLS\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Start with TLS\n76: - **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == true`\n77: - **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n78: - **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)` SHALL be called\n79: - AND error SHALL be returned if cert/key files are missing\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Graceful shutdown\n82: - **GIVEN** a running `Server`\n83: - **WHEN** context is cancelled\n84: - **THEN** `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` SHALL be called\n85: - AND shutdown deadline SHALL be `10s`\n86: - AND server SHALL stop accepting new connections\n87: - AND existing connections SHALL complete\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Server timeouts\n90: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n91: - **WHEN** initializing `httpServer`\n92: - **THEN** timeouts SHALL be configured:\n93:   - `ReadTimeout` = `30s`\n94:   - `IdleTimeout` = `90s`\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### Requirement: Route registration\n99: \n100: The system SHALL register routes for health endpoints and invocation paths.\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Health routes\n103: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n104: - **WHEN** registering routes\n105: - **THEN** `/health/live` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthLive`\n106: - AND `/health/ready` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthReady`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Invocation routes\n109: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n110: - **WHEN** registering routes\n111: - **THEN** `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n112: - AND `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n113: - AND both `GET` and `POST` methods SHALL be supported\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Middleware chain\n116: - **GIVEN** route registration\n117: - **WHEN** applying middleware\n118: - **THEN** `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` SHALL be applied globally\n119: - AND `loggingMiddleware` SHALL be applied for request logging\n120: - AND `recoveryMiddleware` SHALL be applied for panic recovery\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: SessionManager interface\n125: \n126: The system SHALL define `SessionManager` interface for session resolution and sandbox creation.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: SessionManager interface definition\n129: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n130: - **WHEN** reading the `SessionManager` interface\n131: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n132:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: manager struct definition\n135: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n136: - **WHEN** reading the `manager` struct\n137: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n138:   - `storeClient Store` for session lookup\n139:   - `workloadMgrAddr string` for Workload Manager URL\n140:   - `httpClient *http.Client` for sandbox creation requests\n141:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: NewSessionManager constructor\n144: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n145: - **WHEN** calling `NewSessionManager(store Store, logger Logger)`\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*manager` with:\n147:   - `workloadMgrAddr` from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n148:   - startup SHALL fail if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is not set\n149:   - `httpClient` with `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: HTTP client configuration\n152: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n153: - **WHEN** initializing `httpClient`\n154: - **THEN** HTTP2 SHALL be configured with:\n155:   - `ReadIdleTimeout` = `30s`\n156:   - `PingTimeout` = `15s`\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: Session resolution\n161: \n162: The system SHALL resolve sessions by ID and create new sandboxes when missing.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession with existing session\n165: - **GIVEN** a session ID that exists in store\n166: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n167: - **THEN** `store.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n168: - AND `*SandboxInfo` SHALL be returned if found\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession creates new sandbox\n171: - **GIVEN** a session ID that does NOT exist in store\n172: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n173: - **THEN** `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n174: - AND POST request SHALL be sent to Workload Manager\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: createSandbox POST request\n177: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n178: - **WHEN** calling `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n179: - **THEN** POST SHALL be sent to:\n180:   - `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n181:   - `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n182: - AND request body SHALL be `CreateSandboxRequest`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: createSandbox with K8s SA token\n185: - **GIVEN** in-cluster deployment\n186: - **WHEN** sending POST to Workload Manager\n187: - **THEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` SHALL be read\n188: - AND token SHALL be set as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: createSandbox namespace\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n192: - **WHEN** creating sandbox\n193: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read for target namespace\n194: - AND default namespace SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy implementation\n199: \n200: The system SHALL implement reverse proxy with custom Director and error handling.\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: ReverseProxy struct definition\n203: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n204: - **WHEN** reading the implementation\n205: - **THEN** `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` SHALL be used as base\n206: - AND custom `Director` function SHALL be set\n207: - AND custom `ModifyResponse` function SHALL be set\n208: - AND custom `ErrorHandler` function SHALL be set\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Director path normalization\n211: - **GIVEN** a request with path `/api/run`\n212: - **WHEN** Director processes the request\n213: - **THEN** leading slash SHALL be prefixed if missing: `//api/run` → `/api/run`\n214: - AND path SHALL match entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Director forwarding headers\n217: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n218: - **WHEN** Director processes request\n219: - **THEN** `req.Host` SHALL be set to target host\n220: - AND `X-Forwarded-For` SHALL be set with client IP\n221: - AND `X-Real-IP` SHALL be set with client IP\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Director JWT injection\n224: - **GIVEN** a proxied request\n225: - **WHEN** Director processes request\n226: - **THEN** JWT token SHALL be generated by `jwtManager`\n227: - AND `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` SHALL be added to request headers\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: ModifyResponse session header injection\n230: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n231: - **WHEN** ModifyResponse processes response\n232: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be added to response\n233: - AND value SHALL be the resolved session ID\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: ErrorHandler connection refused\n236: - **GIVEN** proxy error with connection refused\n237: - **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n238: - **THEN** HTTP `502` SHALL be returned\n239: - AND error code SHALL be `sandbox unreachable`\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: ErrorHandler timeout\n242: - **GIVEN** proxy error with timeout\n243: - **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n244: - **THEN** HTTP `504` SHALL be returned\n245: - AND error code SHALL be `sandbox timeout`\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Entry point matching\n248: - **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` with multiple entry points\n249: - **WHEN** selecting entry point\n250: - **THEN** first entry point with matching path prefix SHALL be used\n251: - AND `Endpoint` SHALL be the proxy target URL\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ### Requirement: JWT Manager\n256: \n257: The system SHALL implement JWT token generation with RSA signing and K8s Secret persistence.\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: JWTManager interface definition\n260: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n261: - **WHEN** reading the `JWTManager` interface\n262: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n263:   - `GenerateToken(ctx context.Context, kind, name, namespace string) (string, error)`\n264:   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error`\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: jwtManager struct definition\n267: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n268: - **WHEN** reading the `jwtManager` struct\n269: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n270:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey` for RSA private key\n271:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` for RSA public key\n272:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for K8s Secret operations\n273:   - `namespace string` for Secret namespace\n274:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: RSA key generation\n277: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n278: - **WHEN** generating RSA key\n279: - **THEN** `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)` SHALL be called\n280: - AND key size SHALL be `2048` bits (constant `rsaKeySize`)\n281: - AND private key SHALL be PKCS1 encoded\n282: - AND public key SHALL be PKIX encoded\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: GenerateToken\n285: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n286: - **WHEN** calling `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)`\n287: - **THEN** JWT SHALL be created with claims:\n288:   - `exp` = `now + 5m` (constant `jwtExpiration`)\n289:   - `iat` = `now`\n290:   - `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`\n291:   - `kind` = kind parameter\n292:   - `name` = name parameter\n293:   - `namespace` = namespace parameter\n294: - AND JWT SHALL be signed with RS256 algorithm\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret create\n297: - **GIVEN** no existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n298: - **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n299: - **THEN** K8s Secret SHALL be created with:\n300:   - `name` = `IdentitySecretName` (`\"picod-router-identity\"`)\n301:   - `data[\"private-key\"]` = PKCS1 encoded private key\n302:   - `data[\"public-key\"]` = PKIX encoded public key\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret load\n305: - **GIVEN** existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n306: - **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n307: - **THEN** Secret SHALL be loaded via `kubeClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Get`\n308: - AND keys SHALL be decoded from Secret data\n309: - AND `privateKey` and `publicKey` SHALL be set from loaded data\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret AlreadyExists\n312: - **GIVEN** multiple router replicas starting simultaneously\n313: - **WHEN** Secret creation returns `AlreadyExists` error\n314: - **THEN** existing Secret SHALL be loaded instead\n315: - AND no error SHALL be returned\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: Middleware concurrency limit\n320: \n321: The system SHALL limit concurrent requests using semaphore middleware.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: concurrencyLimitMiddleware\n324: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n325: - **WHEN** reading middleware implementation\n326: - **THEN** buffered channel SHALL be used as semaphore\n327: - AND channel capacity SHALL be `MaxConcurrentRequests`\n328: - AND default capacity SHALL be `1000` when `MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0`\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Request acquires semaphore\n331: - **GIVEN** middleware with capacity 1000\n332: - **WHEN** request enters middleware\n333: - **THEN** `semaphore <- struct{}{}` SHALL acquire slot\n334: - AND request SHALL proceed if slot available\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Semaphore full returns 429\n337: - **GIVEN** middleware with all slots occupied\n338: - **WHEN** new request enters middleware\n339: - **THEN** `select` with `default` case SHALL trigger\n340: - AND HTTP `429` SHALL be returned\n341: - AND response body SHALL have `SERVER_OVERLOADED` code\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Request releases semaphore\n344: - **GIVEN** request completing processing\n345: - **WHEN** middleware exits\n346: - **THEN** `<-semaphore` SHALL release slot\n347: - AND deferred release SHALL guarantee cleanup\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ### Requirement: Health handlers\n352: \n353: The system SHALL implement health endpoints for Kubernetes probes.\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: handleHealthLive\n356: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n357: - **WHEN** calling `/health/live`\n358: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n359: - AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager nil\n362: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n363: - **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with `sessionManager == nil`\n364: - **THEN** HTTP `503` SHALL be returned\n365: - AND body SHALL indicate service unavailable\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager set\n368: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n369: - **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with valid `sessionManager`\n370: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n371: - AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ### Requirement: Invocation handler\n376: \n377: The system SHALL implement invocation handler for proxying requests to sandboxes.\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: handleInvoke extracts session ID\n380: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n381: - **WHEN** processing invocation request\n382: - **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be read\n383: - AND session ID SHALL be extracted for session resolution\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: handleInvoke resolves session\n386: - **GIVEN** request with session ID header\n387: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n388: - **THEN** `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n389: - AND `namespace`, `name`, `kind` SHALL be extracted from URL path\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: handleInvoke creates new session\n392: - **GIVEN** request without session ID header\n393: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n394: - **THEN** new session ID SHALL be generated\n395: - AND new sandbox SHALL be created via session manager\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: handleInvoke proxies request\n398: - **GIVEN** resolved `SandboxInfo`\n399: - **WHEN** processing invocation\n400: - **THEN** reverse proxy SHALL forward request to `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint`\n401: - AND request body SHALL be forwarded unchanged\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: handleInvoke updates activity\n404: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n405: - **WHEN** invocation completes\n406: - **THEN** `store.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n407: - AND `LastActivity` timestamp SHALL be updated twice:\n408:   - After sandbox resolution\n409:   - After proxy completion\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: handleInvoke error mapping\n412: - **GIVEN** an error from session resolution or proxy\n413: - **WHEN** returning response\n414: - **THEN** error type SHALL map to HTTP code:\n415:   - `SessionNotFoundError` → `404`\n416:   - `SandboxUnreachableError` → `502`\n417:   - `TimeoutError` → `504`\n418:   - `JWTSigningFailedError` → `500`\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: Error types\n423: \n424: The system SHALL define custom error types for categorizing failures.\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: SessionNotFoundError\n427: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n428: - **WHEN** reading error types\n429: - **THEN** `SessionNotFoundError` SHALL be defined\n430: - AND error code SHALL be `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: SandboxUnreachableError\n433: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n434: - **WHEN** reading error types\n435: - **THEN** `SandboxUnreachableError` SHALL be defined\n436: - AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: TimeoutError\n439: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n440: - **WHEN** reading error types\n441: - **THEN** `TimeoutError` SHALL be defined\n442: - AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: JWTSigningFailedError\n445: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n446: - **WHEN** reading error types\n447: - **THEN** `JWTSigningFailedError` SHALL be defined\n448: - AND error code SHALL be `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: ServerOverloadedError\n451: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n452: - **WHEN** reading error types\n453: - **THEN** `ServerOverloadedError` SHALL be defined\n454: - AND error code SHALL be `SERVER_OVERLOADED`\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: APIStatus interface\n457: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n458: - **WHEN** reading error types\n459: - **THEN** `APIStatus` interface SHALL be defined with:\n460:   - `Status() int` for HTTP status code\n461:   - `Code() string` for error code\n462:   - `Message() string` for error message\n463: \n464: ---\n465: \n466: ### Requirement: Store interface usage\n467: \n468: The system SHALL use Store interface for session state operations.\n469: \n470: #### Scenario: Store interface methods\n471: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n472: - **WHEN** using Store interface\n473: - **THEN** methods SHALL be used:\n474:   - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n475:   - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n476:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ### Requirement: Environment variables\n481: \n482: The system SHALL read configuration from environment variables.\n483: \n484: #### Scenario: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n485: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n486: - **WHEN** initializing SessionManager\n487: - **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable SHALL be required\n488: - AND startup SHALL fail if not set\n489: \n490: #### Scenario: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n491: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n492: - **WHEN** determining namespace for sandbox creation\n493: - **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read\n494: - AND default SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n495: \n496: ---\n497: \n498: ### Requirement: Constants\n499: \n500: The system SHALL define constants for configuration values.\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: rsaKeySize constant\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading constants\n505: - **THEN** `rsaKeySize` SHALL be `2048`\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: jwtExpiration constant\n508: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n509: - **WHEN** reading constants\n510: - **THEN** `jwtExpiration` SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n511: \n512: #### Scenario: IdentitySecretName constant\n513: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n514: - **WHEN** reading constants\n515: - **THEN** `IdentitySecretName` SHALL be `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Server\n520: \n521: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for Server behavior.\n522: \n523: #### Scenario: TestNewServer\n524: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n525: - **WHEN** running tests\n526: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n527:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n528:   - Gin mode is set correctly based on Debug config\n529:   - All fields are properly initialized\n530: \n531: #### Scenario: TestServer_StartTLS\n532: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n533: - **WHEN** running tests\n534: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n535:   - TLS server starts with valid cert/key\n536:   - Error returned for missing cert/key files\n537: \n538: #### Scenario: TestServer_GracefulShutdown\n539: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n540: - **WHEN** running tests\n541: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n542:   - Server stops on context cancellation\n543:   - Shutdown deadline is 10s\n544:   - Existing requests complete before shutdown\n545: \n546: #### Scenario: TestServer_Routes\n547: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n548: - **WHEN** running tests\n549: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n550:   - Health routes are registered\n551:   - Invocation routes are registered\n552:   - Middleware chain is applied\n553: \n554: ---\n555: \n556: ### Requirement: Unit tests for SessionManager\n557: \n558: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SessionManager.\n559: \n560: #### Scenario: TestNewSessionManager\n561: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n562: - **WHEN** running tests\n563: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n564:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n565:   - Fails when WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL not set\n566:   - HTTP client configured correctly\n567: \n568: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Existing\n569: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n570: - **WHEN** running tests with existing session\n571: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n572:   - Store lookup is called\n573:   - SandboxInfo returned correctly\n574: \n575: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Create\n576: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n577: - **WHEN** running tests with missing session\n578: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n579:   - POST request sent to Workload Manager\n580:   - Correct endpoint based on kind\n581:   - Sandbox created and stored\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: TestSessionManager_createSandbox\n584: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n585: - **WHEN** running tests\n586: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n587:   - Request body is CreateSandboxRequest\n588:   - K8s SA token added when available\n589:   - Error handling for failed requests\n590: \n591: ---\n592: \n593: ### Requirement: Unit tests for ReverseProxy\n594: \n595: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for reverse proxy.\n596: \n597: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_Director\n598: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n599: - **WHEN** running tests\n600: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n601:   - Path normalization adds leading slash\n602:   - Forwarding headers are set\n603:   - JWT is injected\n604: \n605: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ModifyResponse\n606: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n607: - **WHEN** running tests\n608: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n609:   - Session ID header added to response\n610: \n611: #### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ErrorHandler\n612: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n613: - **WHEN** running tests\n614: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n615:   - Connection refused → 502\n616:   - Timeout → 504\n617:   - Other errors → 500\n618: \n619: ---\n620: \n621: ### Requirement: Unit tests for JWTManager\n622: \n623: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for JWT operations.\n624: \n625: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_GenerateToken\n626: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n627: - **WHEN** running tests\n628: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n629:   - Token contains correct claims\n630:   - Token is signed with RS256\n631:   - Token expires in 5 minutes\n632: \n633: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_RSAKeyGeneration\n634: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n635: - **WHEN** running tests\n636: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n637:   - Key size is 2048 bits\n638:   - Keys are valid RSA keys\n639: \n640: #### Scenario: TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret\n641: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n642: - **WHEN** running tests\n643: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n644:   - Secret created when not exists\n645:   - Secret loaded when exists\n646:   - AlreadyExists handled gracefully\n647: \n648: ---\n649: \n650: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Middleware\n651: \n652: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for concurrency middleware.\n653: \n654: #### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware\n655: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n656: - **WHEN** running tests\n657: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n658:   - Requests proceed when slots available\n659:   - 429 returned when full\n660:   - Slots released after request completes\n661: \n662: #### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_DefaultCapacity\n663: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n664: - **WHEN** running tests with MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0\n665: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n666:   - Capacity defaults to 1000\n667: \n668: ---\n669: \n670: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Handlers\n671: \n672: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for handlers.\n673: \n674: #### Scenario: TestHandleHealthLive\n675: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n676: - **WHEN** running tests\n677: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n678:   - Returns 200 with {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n679: \n680: #### Scenario: TestHandleHealthReady\n681: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n682: - **WHEN** running tests\n683: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n684:   - Returns 200 when sessionManager valid\n685:   - Returns 503 when sessionManager nil\n686: \n687: #### Scenario: TestHandleInvoke\n688: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n689: - **WHEN** running tests\n690: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n691:   - Session ID extracted from header\n692:   - New session created when missing\n693:   - Request proxied to sandbox endpoint\n694:   - Activity timestamp updated\n695: \n696: ---\n697: \n698: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Errors\n699: \n700: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for error types.\n701: \n702: #### Scenario: TestErrorTypes\n703: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n704: - **WHEN** running tests\n705: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n706:   - All error types implement APIStatus\n707:   - Status codes are correct\n708:   - Error codes are correct\n709: \n710: ---\n711: \n712: ### Requirement: File structure\n713: \n714: The system SHALL organize router files correctly.\n715: \n716: #### Scenario: server.go location\n717: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n718: - **WHEN** listing files\n719: - **THEN** `server.go` SHALL exist with Server implementation\n720: \n721: #### Scenario: config.go location\n722: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n723: - **WHEN** listing files\n724: - **THEN** `config.go` SHALL exist with Config struct\n725: \n726: #### Scenario: session_manager.go location\n727: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n728: - **WHEN** listing files\n729: - **THEN** `session_manager.go` SHALL exist with SessionManager\n730: \n731: #### Scenario: reverse_proxy.go location\n732: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n733: - **WHEN** listing files\n734: - **THEN** `reverse_proxy.go` SHALL exist with proxy implementation\n735: \n736: #### Scenario: jwt.go location\n737: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n738: - **WHEN** listing files\n739: - **THEN** `jwt.go` SHALL exist with JWTManager\n740: \n741: #### Scenario: middleware.go location\n742: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n743: - **WHEN** listing files\n744: - **THEN** `middleware.go` SHALL exist with concurrency middleware\n745: \n746: #### Scenario: handlers.go location\n747: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n748: - **WHEN** listing files\n749: - **THEN** `handlers.go` SHALL exist with health and invocation handlers\n750: \n751: #### Scenario: errors.go location\n752: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n753: - **WHEN** listing files\n754: - **THEN** `errors.go` SHALL exist with error types\n755: \n756: #### Scenario: Test files location\n757: - **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n758: - **WHEN** listing files\n759: - **THEN** `*_test.go` SHALL exist for each implementation file\n760: \n761: ---\n762: \n763: ## Implementation Files\n764: \n765: | File | Purpose |\n766: |------|---------|\n767: | `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle |\n768: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server unit tests |\n769: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests |\n770: | `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Config unit tests |\n771: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface and implementation |\n772: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | SessionManager unit tests |\n773: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Reverse proxy with Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n774: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Reverse proxy unit tests |\n775: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation, token signing |\n776: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT unit tests |\n777: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limit middleware |\n778: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n779: | `pkg/router/handlers.go` | Health and invocation handlers |\n780: | `pkg/router/handlers_test.go` | Handlers unit tests |\n781: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Error types with APIStatus interface |\n782: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Error types unit tests |\n783: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n784: \n785: ---\n786: \n787: ## Dependencies\n788: \n789: | Package | Purpose |\n790: |---------|---------|\n791: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for routing and middleware |\n792: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | RS256 JWT signing |\n793: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | h2c server configuration |\n794: | `net/http/httputil` | ReverseProxy for request forwarding |\n795: | `crypto/rsa` | RSA key generation and signing |\n796: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API for Secret management |\n797: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants |\n798: | `pkg/store` | Store interface for session lookup and activity updates |\n799: \n800: ---\n801: \n802: ## Request Flow\n803: \n804: ```\n805: Client Request\n806: │\n807: ├── Middleware Chain\n808: │   ├── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore acquire)\n809: │   ├── loggingMiddleware\n810: │   └── recoveryMiddleware\n811: │\n812: ├── Handler: handleInvoke\n813: │   ├── Extract session ID from x-agentcube-session-id header\n814: │   ├── If missing: Generate new session ID\n815: │   │\n816: │   ├── SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession\n817: │   │   ├── Check store for existing session\n818: │   │   ├── If not found: createSandbox\n819: │   │   │   ├── POST to Workload Manager\n820: │   │   │   │   ├── /v1/agent-runtime (AgentRuntime)\n821: │   │   │   │   └── /v1/code-interpreter (CodeInterpreter)\n822: │   │   │   ├── With K8s SA token if available\n823: │   │   │   └── Store sandbox info\n824: │   │   └── Update activity timestamp (1st)\n825: │   │\n826: │   ├── ReverseProxy.ServeHTTP\n827: │   │   ├── Director\n828: │   │   │   ├── Path normalization (add leading slash)\n829: │   │   │   ├── Set Host, X-Forwarded-For, X-Real-IP\n830: │   │   │   ├── JWTManager.GenerateToken → Authorization header\n831: │   │   │   └── Target: SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint\n832: │   │   ├── Forward to sandbox pod\n833: │   │   ├── ModifyResponse\n834: │   │   │   └── Add x-agentcube-session-id header\n835: │   │   └── ErrorHandler\n836: │   │       ├── Connection refused → 502\n837: │   │       └── Timeout → 504\n838: │   │\n839: │   └── Update activity timestamp (2nd)\n840: │\n841: └── Middleware Chain (exit)\n842:     └── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore release)\n843: ```\n844: \n845: ---\n846: \n847: ## Error Mapping\n848: \n849: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Condition |\n850: |------------|-------------|------------|-----------|\n851: | `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | Session not in store |\n852: | `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | Connection refused to pod |\n853: | `TimeoutError` | 504 | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | Proxy timeout |\n854: | `JWTSigningFailedError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | JWT generation failure |\n855: | `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | Semaphore full |\n856: | `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | Empty EntryPoints array |\n857: \n858: ---\n859: \n860: ## Configuration Values\n861: \n862: | Parameter | Default | Source | Description |\n863: |-----------|---------|--------|-------------|\n864: | `Port` | 8080 | Config | Listening port |\n865: | `EnableTLS` | false | Config | TLS enablement |\n866: | `TLSCert` | \"\" | Config | Certificate file path |\n867: | `TLSKey` | \"\" | Config | Private key file path |\n868: | `MaxConcurrentRequests` | 1000 | Config | Semaphore capacity |\n869: | `ReadTimeout` | 30s | Server | HTTP read timeout |\n870: | `IdleTimeout` | 90s | Server | HTTP idle timeout |\n871: | `ShutdownTimeout` | 10s | Server | Graceful shutdown deadline |\n872: | `rsaKeySize` | 2048 | Const | RSA key bits |\n873: | `jwtExpiration` | 5m | Const | JWT validity duration |\n874: | `IdentitySecretName` | picod-router-identity | Const | JWT Secret name |\n875: | `HttpClientTimeout` | 2m | SessionManager | HTTP client timeout |\n876: | `MaxIdleConnsPerHost` | 100 | SessionManager | Connection pool size |\n877: | `HTTP2ReadIdleTimeout` | 30s | SessionManager | HTTP2 read idle |\n878: | `HTTP2PingTimeout` | 15s | SessionManager | HTTP2 ping timeout |\n879: \n880: ---\n881: \n882: ## Environment Variables\n883: \n884: | Variable | Required | Default | Usage |\n885: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n886: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | - | Workload Manager service URL |\n887: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | default | Namespace for sandbox creation |\n888: \n889: ---\n890: \n891: ## Validation Checklist\n892: \n893: - [ ] Server struct defined with all required fields\n894: - [ ] Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests\n895: - [ ] NewServer constructor initializes Gin engine\n896: - [ ] Gin mode set based on Debug config\n897: - [ ] Server.Start supports TLS and non-TLS\n898: - [ ] Graceful shutdown with 10s deadline\n899: - [ ] Health routes registered (/health/live, /health/ready)\n900: - [ ] Invocation routes registered with GET and POST\n901: - [ ] Middleware chain applied (concurrency, logging, recovery)\n902: - [ ] SessionManager interface defined\n903: - [ ] GetSandboxBySession resolves or creates sessions\n904: - [ ] createSandbox POST to Workload Manager\n905: - [ ] K8s SA token added for in-cluster auth\n906: - [ ] ReverseProxy with custom Director\n907: - [ ] Director normalizes path and injects JWT\n908: - [ ] ModifyResponse adds session header\n909: - [ ] ErrorHandler maps errors to HTTP codes\n910: - [ ] JWTManager with RSA key generation\n911: - [ ] GenerateToken with RS256, 5m expiration\n912: - [ ] TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret handles creation/loading\n913: - [ ] AlreadyExists handled for concurrent routers\n914: - [ ] concurrencyLimitMiddleware with semaphore\n915: - [ ] 429 returned when overloaded\n916: - [ ] handleHealthLive returns 200\n917: - [ ] handleHealthReady checks sessionManager\n918: - [ ] handleInvoke proxies to sandbox\n919: - [ ] Activity timestamp updated twice\n920: - [ ] Error types implement APIStatus\n921: - [ ] WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required\n922: - [ ] AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE with default\n923: - [ ] Constants defined (rsaKeySize, jwtExpiration, IdentitySecretName)\n924: - [ ] Unit tests for all components\n925: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n926: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n927: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 927 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Server type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775852297871,"end":1775852297885}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852297890,"sessionID":"ses_286f4e666ffednMOyI47LTqQHL","part":{"id":"prt_d790b9e74001TcQWJ6UQcbIaVf","messageID":"msg_d790b7707001wt2EZgD2R9a0Zc","sessionID":"ses_286f4e666ffednMOyI47LTqQHL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-efe4a8d8482a4c8caa248a40e3681eb0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/middleware_test.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/middleware_test.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"net/http\"\n5: \t\"net/http/httptest\"\n6: \t\"sync\"\n7: \t\"testing\"\n8: \t\"time\"\n9: \n10: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n11: )\n12: \n13: type MockLogger struct {\n14: \tInfoCalls    []string\n15: \tErrorCalls   []string\n16: \tWarningCalls []string\n17: }\n18: \n19: func (m *MockLogger) Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...any) {\n20: \tm.InfoCalls = append(m.InfoCalls, msg)\n21: }\n22: \n23: func (m *MockLogger) Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...any) {\n24: \tm.ErrorCalls = append(m.ErrorCalls, msg)\n25: }\n26: \n27: func (m *MockLogger) Warning(msg string, keysAndValues ...any) {\n28: \tm.WarningCalls = append(m.WarningCalls, msg)\n29: }\n30: \n31: func TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareUnderLimit(t *testing.T) {\n32: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n33: \n34: \trouter := gin.New()\n35: \trouter.Use(concurrencyLimitMiddleware(10))\n36: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n37: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n38: \t})\n39: \n40: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n41: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n42: \n43: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n44: \n45: \tif w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n46: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected status code: %d\", w.Code)\n47: \t}\n48: }\n49: \n50: func TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareOverLimit(t *testing.T) {\n51: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n52: \n53: \trouter := gin.New()\n54: \trouter.Use(concurrencyLimitMiddleware(1))\n55: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n56: \t\ttime.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)\n57: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n58: \t})\n59: \n60: \tvar wg sync.WaitGroup\n61: \tresults := make([]int, 3)\n62: \n63: \tfor i := 0; i < 3; i++ {\n64: \t\twg.Add(1)\n65: \t\tgo func(idx int) {\n66: \t\t\tdefer wg.Done()\n67: \t\t\treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n68: \t\t\tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n69: \t\t\trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n70: \t\t\tresults[idx] = w.Code\n71: \t\t}(i)\n72: \t}\n73: \n74: \twg.Wait()\n75: \n76: \thasOverloaded := false\n77: \thasOk := false\n78: \tfor _, code := range results {\n79: \t\tif code == http.StatusTooManyRequests {\n80: \t\t\thasOverloaded = true\n81: \t\t}\n82: \t\tif code == http.StatusOK {\n83: \t\t\thasOk = true\n84: \t\t}\n85: \t}\n86: \n87: \tif !hasOverloaded {\n88: \t\tt.Error(\"expected at least one 429 response\")\n89: \t}\n90: \tif !hasOk {\n91: \t\tt.Error(\"expected at least one 200 response\")\n92: \t}\n93: }\n94: \n95: func TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareDefault(t *testing.T) {\n96: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n97: \n98: \trouter := gin.New()\n99: \trouter.Use(concurrencyLimitMiddleware(0))\n100: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n101: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n102: \t})\n103: \n104: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n105: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n106: \n107: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n108: \n109: \tif w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n110: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected status code with default limit: %d\", w.Code)\n111: \t}\n112: }\n113: \n114: func TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareNegative(t *testing.T) {\n115: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n116: \n117: \trouter := gin.New()\n118: \trouter.Use(concurrencyLimitMiddleware(-5))\n119: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n120: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n121: \t})\n122: \n123: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n124: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n125: \n126: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n127: \n128: \tif w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n129: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected status code with negative limit: %d\", w.Code)\n130: \t}\n131: }\n132: \n133: func TestLoggingMiddleware(t *testing.T) {\n134: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n135: \n136: \tlogger := &MockLogger{}\n137: \trouter := gin.New()\n138: \trouter.Use(loggingMiddleware(logger))\n139: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n140: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n141: \t})\n142: \n143: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n144: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n145: \n146: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n147: \n148: \tif len(logger.InfoCalls) != 1 {\n149: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected 1 info log call, got %d\", len(logger.InfoCalls))\n150: \t}\n151: \tif logger.InfoCalls[0] != \"request\" {\n152: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected log message: %s\", logger.InfoCalls[0])\n153: \t}\n154: }\n155: \n156: func TestLoggingMiddlewareDifferentStatus(t *testing.T) {\n157: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n158: \n159: \tlogger := &MockLogger{}\n160: \trouter := gin.New()\n161: \trouter.Use(loggingMiddleware(logger))\n162: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n163: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusInternalServerError, gin.H{\"error\": \"internal\"})\n164: \t})\n165: \n166: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n167: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n168: \n169: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n170: \n171: \tif len(logger.InfoCalls) != 1 {\n172: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected 1 info log call, got %d\", len(logger.InfoCalls))\n173: \t}\n174: }\n175: \n176: func TestRecoveryMiddleware(t *testing.T) {\n177: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n178: \n179: \tlogger := &MockLogger{}\n180: \trouter := gin.New()\n181: \trouter.Use(recoveryMiddleware(logger))\n182: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n183: \t\tpanic(\"test panic\")\n184: \t})\n185: \n186: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n187: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n188: \n189: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n190: \n191: \tif w.Code != http.StatusInternalServerError {\n192: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected status code: %d\", w.Code)\n193: \t}\n194: \tif len(logger.ErrorCalls) != 1 {\n195: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected 1 error log call, got %d\", len(logger.ErrorCalls))\n196: \t}\n197: }\n198: \n199: func TestRecoveryMiddlewareNoPanic(t *testing.T) {\n200: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n201: \n202: \tlogger := &MockLogger{}\n203: \trouter := gin.New()\n204: \trouter.Use(recoveryMiddleware(logger))\n205: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n206: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n207: \t})\n208: \n209: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n210: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n211: \n212: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n213: \n214: \tif w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n215: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected status code: %d\", w.Code)\n216: \t}\n217: \tif len(logger.ErrorCalls) != 0 {\n218: \t\tt.Errorf(\"expected 0 error log calls, got %d\", len(logger.ErrorCalls))\n219: \t}\n220: }\n221: \n222: func TestConcurrencyMiddleware429ResponseFormat(t *testing.T) {\n223: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n224: \n225: \trouter := gin.New()\n226: \trouter.Use(concurrencyLimitMiddleware(1))\n227: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n228: \t\ttime.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n229: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{})\n230: \t})\n231: \n232: \tvar wg sync.WaitGroup\n233: \twg.Add(2)\n234: \n235: \tgo func() {\n236: \t\tdefer wg.Done()\n237: \t\treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n238: \t\tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n239: \t\trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n240: \t}()\n241: \n242: \ttime.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\n243: \n244: \tgo func() {\n245: \t\tdefer wg.Done()\n246: \t\treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n247: \t\tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n248: \t\trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n249: \t\tif w.Code == http.StatusTooManyRequests {\n250: \t\t\tbody := w.Body.String()\n251: \t\t\tif !containsStr(body, \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\") {\n252: \t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected SERVER_OVERLOADED in response body\")\n253: \t\t\t}\n254: \t\t}\n255: \t}()\n256: \n257: \twg.Wait()\n258: }\n259: \n260: func containsStr(s, substr string) bool {\n261: \tfor i := 0; i <= len(s)-len(substr); i++ {\n262: \t\tif s[i:i+len(substr)] == substr {\n263: \t\t\treturn true\n264: \t\t}\n265: \t}\n266: \treturn false\n267: }\n268: \n269: func TestNilLoggerMiddleware(t *testing.T) {\n270: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n271: \n272: \trouter := gin.New()\n273: \trouter.Use(loggingMiddleware(nil))\n274: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n275: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n276: \t})\n277: \n278: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n279: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n280: \n281: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n282: \n283: \tif w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n284: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected status code with nil logger: %d\", w.Code)\n285: \t}\n286: }\n287: \n288: func TestNilLoggerRecovery(t *testing.T) {\n289: \tgin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n290: \n291: \trouter := gin.New()\n292: \trouter.Use(recoveryMiddleware(nil))\n293: \trouter.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n294: \t\tpanic(\"test panic\")\n295: \t})\n296: \n297: \treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/test\", nil)\n298: \tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n299: \n300: \trouter.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n301: \n302: \tif w.Code != http.StatusInternalServerError {\n303: \t\tt.Errorf(\"unexpected status code: %d\", w.Code)\n304: \t}\n305: }\n\n(End of file - total 305 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"net/http/httptest\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n)\n\ntype MockLogger struct {\n\tInfoCalls    []string\n\tErrorCalls   []string\n\tWarningCalls []string\n}\n\nfunc (m *MockLogger) Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...any) {\n\tm.InfoCalls = append(m.InfoCalls, msg)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/middleware_test.go","time":{"start":1775852297872,"end":1775852297888}}}}
